{
  "texts": [
    "(Note: There is no statue of Paona Brajabashi in Polo Ground.",
    ")-His ancestral home in Palasa, a small town nestled between the blue-green sweep of paddy fields and the distant shimmer of the Bay of Bengal.",
    "(Note: Palasa town is quite a distance from the coast, so it is inaccurate to say it is nestled between the coast and fields.",
    ")-The familiar humidity of Srikakulam wrapped around him.",
    "(Note: If Sankranthi is one day away, it means Januarywinter in Srikakulam, which is not humid."
  ]
}